### Teste da API do Petshop
### Execute estes comandos no VS Code com a extensão REST Client

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/api/health

###

### 2. Criar Cliente
POST http://localhost:3000/api/clientes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nome": "João Silva",
  "email": "joao@email.com",
  "telefone": "11999999999",
  "endereco": "Rua das Flores, 123"
}

###

### 3. Listar Clientes
GET http://localhost:3000/api/clientes

###

### 4. Criar Pet
POST http://localhost:3000/api/pets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nome": "Rex",
  "especie": "Cachorro",
  "raca": "Golden Retriever",
  "idade": 3,
  "peso": 25.5,
  "observacoes": "Pet muito dócil",
  "clienteId": 1
}

###

### 5. Listar Pets
GET http://localhost:3000/api/pets

###

### 6. Criar Serviço
POST http://localhost:3000/api/servicos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tipo": "Banho e Tosa",
  "descricao": "Banho completo com tosa higiênica",
  "preco": 80.00,
  "dataServico": "2024-01-15T14:00:00Z",
  "clienteId": 1,
  "petId": 1
}

###

### 7. Listar Serviços
GET http://localhost:3000/api/servicos

###

### 8. Buscar Cliente por ID
GET http://localhost:3000/api/clientes/1

###

### 9. Buscar Pet por ID
GET http://localhost:3000/api/pets/1

###

